SIMPLE: somebody
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Somebody
<hw>Some"bod*y</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧m"b⟦ocr⟧d*⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A person unknown or uncertain; a person indeterminate;
some person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jesus said, <qex>Somebody</qex> hath touched me.</q> <rj><qau>Luke
viii. 46.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We must draw in <qex>somebody</qex> that may stand⟦br⟧
'Twixt us and danger.</q> <rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person of consideration or importance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Before these days rose up Theudas, boasting himself to be
<qex>somebody</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Acts v. 36.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somedeal</ent>⟦br⟧
